    <main>
        <!-- Info Box -->
        <section class="info-box">
            <h2>Welcome to British Swim School of Jersey Shore</h2>
            <p>For years, Jersey Shore families in Monmouth and Ocean Counties have trusted British Swim School for expert, safety-first swim instruction. Serving communities from Howell and Freehold to Brick, Toms River, and Asbury Park, we specialize in beginner-friendly lessons rooted in <a href="/education/drowning-prevention-guide.html" style="color: #0284c7;">drowning prevention</a> for infants as young as 6 months through adults.</p>
            <p>Living near the shore means water is part of everyday life. Our curriculum builds real <a href="/education/lake-ocean-safety.html" style="color: #0284c7;">open-water safety awareness</a> alongside swimming skills, so your family can enjoy the beach with confidence. Not sure <a href="/education/when-to-start-swim-lessons.html" style="color: #0284c7;">when to start lessons</a>? We can help.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Quick Info Grid -->
        <section class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-item">
                <h4>Locations</h4>
                <p>Multiple convenient locations throughout Monmouth & Ocean Counties</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
                <h4>Class Sizes</h4>
                <p>4-6 students per certified instructor for personalized attention</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
                <h4>Age Range</h4>
                <p>6 months through adults</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
                <h4>Year-Round</h4>
                <p>Heated indoor pools, classes every month</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Why Choose This School -->
        <section class="why-choose">
            <h2>Why Jersey Shore Families Choose British Swim School</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Certified instructors with beach and open-water safety expertise</li>
                <li>Small class sizes ensure individual attention and faster progression</li>
                <li>Heated indoor pools maintain consistent temperatures year-round</li>
                <li>Safety-first curriculum built on proven teaching methods</li>
                <li>Convenient multiple locations throughout Monmouth and Ocean Counties</li>
                <li>Flexible scheduling with morning, afternoon, and evening classes</li>
                <li>Free consultation and trial lesson before enrollment</li>
                <li>Family and sibling package options available</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Programs Offered -->
        <section class="programs">
            <h2>Programs for Every Age & Stage</h2>
            <div class="program-grid">
                <div class="program-card">
                    <span class="age-badge">6 months - 3 years</span>
                    <h4>Infant & Toddler</h4>
                    <p>Parent-child classes focusing on water comfort, <a href="/education/teach-child-to-float.html" style="color: #0369a1;">floating</a>, and submersion safety. A safe first step for shore families. Learn more about <a href="/education/toddler-water-safety.html" style="color: #0369a1;">toddler water safety</a>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="program-card">
                    <span class="age-badge">3 - 4 years</span>
                    <h4>Pre-School</h4>
                    <p>Independent water exploration with instructor guidance. Building water confidence through play-based learning. See our guide to <a href="/education/swim-milestones-by-age.html" style="color: #0369a1;">swim milestones by age</a>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="program-card">
                    <span class="age-badge">4 - 5 years</span>
                    <h4>Preschool+</h4>
                    <p>Fundamental strokes and water safety awareness. Kids learn to propel themselves and gain real independence in the water.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="program-card">
                    <span class="age-badge">6+ years</span>
                    <h4>School-Age</h4>
                    <p>Comprehensive stroke development, diving, and water survival skills. Building toward independent swimming and strong <a href="/education/pool-safety-rules.html" style="color: #0369a1;">pool safety habits</a>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="program-card">
                    <span class="age-badge">Teens & Adults</span>
                    <h4>Advanced Programs</h4>
                    <p>Technique refinement, competitive training, and <a href="/education/lake-ocean-safety.html" style="color: #0369a1;">open-water safety skills</a>. Whether you're a <a href="/education/water-safety-teens.html" style="color: #0369a1;">teen building water judgment</a> or an <a href="/education/adult-learn-to-swim.html" style="color: #0369a1;">adult learning to swim</a>, we have a program for you.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="program-card">
                    <span class="age-badge">All Ages</span>
                    <h4>Family Classes</h4>
                    <p>Special programming for families learning together. Build water confidence and create lasting memories. Read about <a href="/education/first-swim-lesson.html" style="color: #0369a1;">what to expect at your first lesson</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

