        <!-- FAQ -->
        <section class="faq-section">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About British Swim School Jersey Shore</h2>

            <div class="faq-item active">
                <h4>How do I get started?</h4>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><a href="/contact/" style="color: #0284c7;">Contact us</a> or email waterwisekids.com@gmail.com to schedule a free consultation where we'll assess your child's needs and discuss the best program. You'll also receive a complimentary trial lesson. Read our guide on <a href="/education/first-swim-lesson.html" style="color: #0284c7;">what to expect at the first swim lesson</a> to help you prepare.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>What makes your instructors special?</h4>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>All our instructors hold current certifications from Red Cross and/or Aquatics Council. They receive ongoing training in safety, development, and teaching techniques. Beyond credentials, they're passionate about water safety and genuinely care about each student's progress.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Do you teach ocean/beach safety?</h4>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes. Our instructors understand Jersey Shore conditions and include ocean safety awareness in our curriculum. We teach about currents, tides, and open-water hazards alongside swimming skills. Read our complete guide to <a href="/education/lake-ocean-safety.html" style="color: #0284c7;">lake and ocean safety</a> for more tips you can use at the beach.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>What if my child is afraid of water?</h4>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>We work with water-anxious children every day. Our patient, certified instructors create safe, supportive environments where every child progresses at their own pace. Many of our most confident swimmers started as fearful kids! Read our guide on <a href="/education/fear-of-water.html" style="color: #0284c7;">helping children overcome fear of water</a> for practical tips.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Are classes really year-round?</h4>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes. Our heated indoor pools allow year-round instruction. This consistency is excellent for skill development and ensures you don't have seasonal gaps in your child's progress.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h4>Do you offer private lessons?</h4>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes. We offer private lessons for families preferring one-on-one instruction or with specific goals. Contact us at waterwisekids.com@gmail.com to discuss options and availability.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

